                                          <div class="footnote-item" id="footnote61_ho7cppa"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref61_ho7cppa">61.</a><div class="footnote-text">Australian Government, E-Safety Commissioner, “Recommender Systems and Algorithms — Position Statement”, <a href="https://www.esafety.gov.au/industry/tech-trends-and-challenges/recommender-systems-and-algorithms">https://www.esafety.gov.au/industry/tech-trends-and-challenges/recommender-systems-and-algorithms</a>.</div></div>
                                          <div class="footnote-item" id="footnote62_hkh7lgi"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref62_hkh7lgi">62.</a><div class="footnote-text">Boaz Miller and Isaac Record, “Justified Belief in a Digital Age: On the Epistemic Implications of Secret Internet Technologies”, <em>Episteme, </em>Vol. 10, Special Issue 2, June 2013, 117–134, <a href="https://philarchive.org/archive/MILJBI">https://philarchive.org/archive/MILJBI</a>.</div></div>
                                          <div class="footnote-item" id="footnote63_8tco19q"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref63_8tco19q">63.</a><div class="footnote-text">Katharine Dommett and Peter J. Verovšek, “Promoting Democracy in the Digital Public Sphere: Applying Theoretical Ideals to Online Political Communication”, <em>Journal of the European Institute for Communication and Culture, </em>Vol. 28, Issue 4, 16 September 2021.</div></div>
                                          <div class="footnote-item" id="footnote64_mpq1p86"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref64_mpq1p86">64.</a><div class="footnote-text">Laura Black et al, “‘Wikipedia is Not a Democracy’: Deliberation and Policy-Making in an Online Community”, (paper presented at the International Communication Association conference, Montreal, Canada, 21 May 2008), <a href="https://www.cs.cornell.edu/~danco/research/papers/democracy-black-ica2008.pdf">https://www.cs.cornell.edu/~danco/research/papers/democracy-black-ica2008.pdf</a>.</div></div>
                                          <div class="footnote-item" id="footnote65_fniyf3y"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref65_fniyf3y">65.</a><div class="footnote-text">Nathaniel J. Klemp and Andrew T. Forcehimes, “From Town-Halls to Wikis: Exploring Wikipedia's Implications for Deliberative Democracy”, <em>Journal for Deliberative Democracy</em>, Vol. 6, Issue 2, 20 September 2010, <a href="https://delibdemjournal.org/article/id/380/">https://delibdemjournal.org/article/id/380/</a>.</div></div>
                                          <div class="footnote-item" id="footnote66_pjqh8i5"><a class="footnote-label" href="#footnoteref66_pjqh8i5">66.</a><div class="footnote-text">Claudia Chwalisz, “A New Wave of Deliberative Democracy”, Carnegie Europe, 26 November 2019, <a href="https://carnegieeurope.eu/2019/11/26/new-wave-of-deliberative-democracy-pub-80422">https://carnegieeurope.eu/2019/11/26/new-wave-of-deliberative-democracy-pub-80422</a>.</div></div>
                  </div>
  </dd>
  </div>
</div>

    </div>

    
     
